The paper discusses a novel scheme for secure vehicular communication systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The proposed scheme involves cooperative message verification, which could also be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for intrusion detection, which could be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
